// Semantic direction:
// container_image is an immutable layered filesystem snapshot for running the application.
// multi_stage_build compiles in one stage and copies only the binary to a distroless_base.
// distroless_base contains only the runtime dependencies, minimizing attack surface.
// image_digest is the SHA-256 of the image manifest, used for deterministic pulls.
// oci_spec defines the standard interface between the container_runtime and the kernel.
// namespace_pid, namespace_net, namespace_mnt isolate process, network, and filesystem views.
// cgroup_v2 enforces cpu_limit and memory_limit at the kernel level.
// kubernetes orchestrates containers across a k8s_cluster of k8s_nodes.
// pod is the smallest deployable unit: one or more co-located containers sharing network and volumes.
// pod_init_container runs to completion before the main container starts.
// liveness_probe restarts the container when it fails; readiness_probe excludes it from the lb.
// startup_probe gives slow-starting containers time to become ready before liveness_probe fires.
// deployment manages rolling updates: it creates new pods and removes old ones per deployment_strategy.
// strategy_rolling_update replaces pods gradually; max_unavailable and max_surge bound the process.
// service_k8s provides a stable virtual IP and DNS name for a set of pods.
// type_load_balancer provisions a cloud load balancer to expose the service externally.
// hpa (HorizontalPodAutoscaler) adjusts deployment_replicas based on hpa_metric.
// helm packages Kubernetes manifests into a helm_chart with versioned helm_values.
// helm_upgrade updates a running helm_release to a new chart_version.
// kustomize_overlay applies environment-specific kustomize_patches over a shared kustomize_base.
// pod_security_context sets non-root user, read-only filesystem, and dropped capabilities.

// Primitive flow:
// nc bygg --mål container -> multi_stage_build: compile stage -> binary
//   -> copy binary to distroless_base -> container_image -> push to image_registry
// kubectl apply / helm_install:
//   deployment_spec -> k8s API -> scheduler places pods on k8s_nodes
//   -> container_runtime pulls image_digest -> start container
//   -> liveness_probe + readiness_probe running
// rolling update: new image tag -> helm_upgrade -> deployment
//   -> rolling_update: new pods ready -> old pods removed (max_unavailable/max_surge)
// hpa: CPU > hpa_target_value -> hpa_scale_up -> increase deployment_replicas
// helm_rollback: deployment_strategy recreate or rollback to previous release

// This defines container image building, OCI runtime, Kubernetes deployment,
// autoscaling, service exposure, Helm packaging, and Kustomize overlays.
